MUSHROOM POISONING - KAZAKHSTAN (SOUTH)
*********************************************
A ProMED_maili post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail, a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 16 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail Correspondent Artak Stepanyan<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Fergana ru, 15 Nov 2006 [translated by Corresp.AS; edited]
<http://www.ferghana.ru/news.php?id=4123>

Three children from 6 to 9 years old died due to mushroom poisoning in
South Kazakhstan. So, the number of fatalities in this region has reached
5. Ten more patients in severe condition now are in the ICU of the regional
hospital, according to A. Shamova, the region's deputy director of the
Department of Health.
She said that the first affected people came to the hospital on 6 Nov 2006.
Since then 5-6 new patients seek medical care every day.
According to Interfax-Kazakhstan, 60 people suffered from mushroom
poisoning in Kazakhstan.
A similar outbreak was detected in Kazakhstan 20 years ago.
Mariyash Seitalieva, deputy of the region's sanitary epidemiological
department of region, stated that the case fatality rate is 50-60 percent.
--
